Yes, all of the soldiers bravely say that they are Spartacus, they

00:20:34.656 --> 00:20:39.006
would rather die than give up the identity of their heroic leader.

00:20:39.796 --> 00:20:43.896
As a result, the Romans crucify them all, including Spartacus.

00:20:45.166 --> 00:20:50.816
Unfortunately this is just Hollywood, there is no evidence that this actually happened.

00:20:51.656 --> 00:20:56.266
Most historians agree that Spartacus was killed on the battlefield,

00:20:56.376 --> 00:21:01.136
and would have been thrown into a mass grave like any other soldier.

00:21:01.946 --> 00:21:06.846
The Roman soldier who killed him might not have even known it was

00:21:06.856 --> 00:21:11.186
Spartacus when they killed him, and certainly now we would have no

00:21:11.186 --> 00:21:16.726
chance of identifying who was Spartacus even if the mass grave was found.

00:21:17.666 --> 00:21:22.406
And as for the gladiators who were not killed in the battle, they were

00:21:22.446 --> 00:21:27.756
taken up north to be an example to the world, or at least to other slaves

00:21:27.786 --> 00:21:32.486
and gladiators, of what happens when you rise up against your masters.

00:21:33.156 --> 00:21:38.576
From Capua, just north of Naples where the gladiators first escaped, right

00:21:38.576 --> 00:21:45.966
through to Rome, 6,000 of Spartacus’s men were lined up on the side of the road

00:21:46.116 --> 00:21:52.416
and crucified, with their bodies left there for months as an example to others.

00:21:53.296 --> 00:22:00.266
But while Spartacus’s final resting place may never be known, we may never know what he actually

